\subsection{Result Analysis}\label{result-analysis}

\subsubsection{Classification Results}\label{classification-results}

This section compares the strongest feature-engineered tabular models
with the raw-CIR CNN+Transformer under the current two-path evaluation
design. The intent is not only to rank models, but also to assess
whether end-to-end waveform learning can remain competitive with
domain-engineered representations.

\paragraph{Primary Metric: AUC}\label{primary-metric-auc}

The AUC is the primary comparison metric because it is
threshold-independent and more robust than accuracy to class imbalance
differences between the inline ML evaluation set and the separate DL
evaluation set. Even so, it does not eliminate the fact that the ML and
DL results come from \textbf{different pipelines}. Table 1 summarizes
the reported results.

